      <body>
         <head>Sneer not</head>

            <div>
               <lg>
                  <l>Sneer not, ye cynics, who to school once went</l>
                  <l>And talked with knowledge at her many marts;</l>
                  <l>Who through long days and longer nights have spent</l>
                  <l>Your peace of soul to strengthen mental parts.</l>
                  <l>The worth ye garnered is not self-confined</l>
                  <l>But spread in plenty like a trader’s show;</l>
                  <l>Year in, year out, for all of human kind</l>
                  <l>What you have learned, a countless number know;</l>
                  <l>But rather court the grace that wisdom gives</l>
                  <l>Which simply means—be fearful of thy might;</l>
                  <l>He knows the most who learns and thereby lives</l>
                  <l>To feel his weakness as he strengthens sight.</l>
               </lg>
            </div>
            <closer>
               <name ref="pers:WE1">Winnifred Eaton</name>
            </closer>
            
      </body>
